h3. Summary

It's not possible to edit the Component Lead and assign it to specific users. Below error message is shown:
- {noformat}
The user "username" does not exist.
{noformat}

h3. Steps to Reproduce

# Have a project and some Components (Component One and Two)
# Have a user and rename it (i.e from _John_ to _A_)
# Assign it to users (A: affected user, B: not affected)
# Edit both components

h3. Current Result 

# Component One with _A_ as the Component Lead shows grey avatar icon instead of their uploaded avatar and the old username
#* !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail! 
# Component Two with _B_ as the Component Lead shows the uploaded avatar but when I assign *A* as the new Component Lead, below error is displayed. 
#* !screenshot-2.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Expected Result

# Component One with _A_ as the Component Lead shows their uploaded avatar and the new username
# Able to assign *A* as the new Component Lead in _Component Two_.

h3. Notes

Users can still create a new component with the affected users (A) as the Component Lead, but *not* editing the existing one.

h3. Workaround

Update the component lead using REST API:

{code}curl -D- -u username:password -X PUT --data {see below} -H "Content-Type: application/json" https://instance.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/<component_ID>{code} 

{noformat}
{
"leadUserName": "username"
}
{noformat}

h3.Tips

In order to quickly gather components for the project via REST API:
# Grab Project ID by running a GET
{code}
https://<instance>.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/project/
{code}
# Insert ProjectID into this GET
{code}
https://<instance>.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/project/<ProjectID>/
{code}

A list of all the current components to the project will appear.

